entry.title: Militants Take Cover Amid Elephants, Lions in West Africa's National Parks
entry.content: The U.S. and its allies battle al Qaeda and Islamic State fighters at a bloody crossroads of wildlife, insurgency, geopolitics and military coups.

entry.title: How Starbucks Lost the Top Spot in China's Coffee Race
entry.content: Rival Luckin now leads Starbucks in the world’s second-most-populous nation.

entry.title: For Postwar Gaza, Differences Grow Over Palestinian Leadership Role
entry.content: The Palestinian Authority faces critics for problems in West Bank amid war with Israel.

entry.title: Brazen Burglars Are Crashing Vehicles Into Stores
entry.content: In a tactic called “ram raiding,” burglars drive a stolen vehicle through a storefront and then loot ATMs, guns and other valuables inside.

entry.title: Hundreds of Palestinians Evacuate Gaza's Largest Hospital as Israel Tightens Control
entry.content: At least 450 patients from Gaza City’s besieged Al-Shifa Hospital, some in wheelchairs, began moving toward the enclave’s south.
